<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="577" type="taxonomic history">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="577">Taxonomic history.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="577">
<bibRefCitation author="Beddome, RH" journalOrPublisher="Madras Quarterly Journal of Medical Sciences" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" pagination="1 - 31" refId="B3" refString="Beddome, RH, 1862. Notes upon the land and freshwater snakes of the Madras Presidency. Madras Quarterly Journal of Medical Sciences 5: 1 - 31" title="Notes upon the land and freshwater snakes of the Madras Presidency." volume="5" year="1862">Beddome (1862)</bibRefCitation>
described this species from the Anaimalai and Palani hills. The uniqueness of this species resulted in its being assigned to its own genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Günther, 1864" authorityName="Gunther" authorityYear="1864" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Peltopelor" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Peltopelor" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">Peltopelor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in a subsequent treatment by 
<bibRefCitation author="Guenther, ACLG" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Miscellany" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" refId="B20" refString="Guenther, ACLG, 1864. . The Reptiles of British India. London Printed by the Ray Society, xxvii + 452 pp." title=". The Reptiles of British India. London Printed by the Ray Society, xxvii + 452 pp." year="1864">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Günther">Guenther</normalizedToken>
(1864)
</bibRefCitation>
. Later, 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, MA" journalOrPublisher="Organisms Diversity &amp; Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" publicationUrl="http://faunaofindia.nic.in/PDFVolumes/fbi/016/index.pdf" refId="B53" refString="Smith, MA, 1943. The Fauna of British India, Ceylon and Burma, including the whole of the Indo-Chinese Subregion. Reptilia and Amphibia, Vol. 3., Serpentes, London: Taylor &amp; Francis. http://faunaofindia.nic.in/PDFVolumes/fbi/016/index.pdf" title="The Fauna of British India, Ceylon and Burma, including the whole of the Indo-Chinese Subregion. Reptilia and Amphibia, Vol. 3., Serpentes, London: Taylor &amp; Francis." url="http://faunaofindia.nic.in/PDFVolumes/fbi/016/index.pdf" year="1943">Smith (1943)</bibRefCitation>
subsumed this genus into 
<taxonomicName class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Trimeresurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Trimeresurus" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">Trimeresurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2004.02.008" author="Malhotra, A" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" pagination="83 - 100" refId="B35" refString="Malhotra, A, Thorpe, RS, 2004. A phylogeny of four mitochondrial gene regions suggests a revised taxonomy for Asian pitvipers (Trimeresurus and Ovophis). Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 32: 83 - 100, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2004.02.008" title="A phylogeny of four mitochondrial gene regions suggests a revised taxonomy for Asian pitvipers (Trimeresurus and Ovophis)." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2004.02.008" volume="32" year="2004">Malhotra and Thorpe (2004)</bibRefCitation>
suggested a revised taxonomy for all 
<taxonomicName class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Trimeresurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Trimeresurus" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">Trimeresurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(sensu lato) groups and assigned them to different genera, reinstating 
<taxonomicName authority="Günther, 1864" authorityName="Gunther" authorityYear="1864" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Peltopelor" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Peltopelor" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">Peltopelor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a valid genus (also see 
<bibRefCitation author="Wallach, V" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Bombay Natural History Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" refId="B64" refString="Wallach, V, Williams, KL, Boundy, J, 2014. Snakes of the World: a Catalogue of Living and Extinct Species. Boca Raton (Florida): CRC Press (Taylor &amp; Francis Group), 1209 pp." title="Snakes of the World: a Catalogue of Living and Extinct Species. Boca Raton (Florida): CRC Press (Taylor &amp; Francis Group), 1209 pp." year="2014">Wallach et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
